The Ultimate Geologists Handbook: Advanced Mining Techniques

Because all ore veins are rather wide, one can space out their strip mines a small distance. A measure of 4 meters between tunnels appears to be the most efficient.
Ore clouds are so rich that even the surface above them has a low ore concentration. Small clusters of low-density ore can be found in the dirt right under the grass. 
The most effective way to find a cloud is to simply shovel out a hollow ditch and with for telltale ore clusters.
